---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="AI-Assisted Cross-Border FinCrime Analyst Review | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>AI-Assisted Cross-Border FinCrime Analyst Review</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard is engineered for high-risk, human-reviewed workflows where AI output may assist a regulated decision path, while policy
      control remains deterministic and reviewable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Workflow Context</h2>
    <p>
      In this workflow, AI can assist analysis for cross-border AML and fraud review, but no inference decision proceeds without BeaconGuard
      approval and structured evidence emission.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>The Enforcement Sequence</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Application Input:</strong> The financial or analyst application submits a cross-border case for AI-assisted summarization or recommendation.</li>
      <li><strong>Gateway Intake:</strong> BeaconGuard intercepts the payload.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Trust &amp; Replay Validation:</strong> The payload is cryptographically validated and checked for replay.
        <strong>Deny path is executed if invalid.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Deterministic Policy Evaluation:</strong> The request is checked against governed policy constraints for required AML, KYC, or workflow evidence.
        <strong>Deny path is executed if incomplete or out of bounds.</strong>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Control Outcome:</strong> BeaconGuard returns an explicit control outcome after deterministic policy enforcement.</li>
      <li><strong>Decision Evidence:</strong> A structured JSON decision record is retained for architecture review and security inspection.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="infra-diagram workflow-frame">
      <div class="workflow-grid">
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-primary wf-node" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 1">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Analyst / Financial Application</p>
          <p>Case context arrives for review.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-boundary wf-node" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1">
          <p class="flow-step-title">BeaconGuard Gateway Intake</p>
          <p>Central control entry and request normalization.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-boundary wf-node" style="grid-column: 3; grid-row: 1">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Trust / Replay</p>
          <p>Signature, nonce, and replay state are validated.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-right" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 2">→</div>
        <div class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-right" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 2">→</div>
        <div class="wf-cell-spacer" style="grid-column: 3; grid-row: 2"></div>

        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-boundary wf-node wf-sequence-step" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 3">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Deterministic Policy Evaluation</p>
          <p>AML/KYC and compliance signals are evaluated.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-down" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 4">↓</div>

        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-evidence wf-node wf-sequence-step" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 5">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Control Outcome</p>
          <p>Explicit allow or deny result.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-arrows" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 6; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <span class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-branch">↓</span>
          <span class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-branch">↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-row" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 7; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-primary wf-node wf-branch-step">
          <p class="flow-step-title">ALLOW</p>
          <p>Request proceeds to bounded model interaction.</p>
        </div>
          <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-deny wf-node wf-branch-step">
          <p class="flow-step-title">DENY</p>
          <p>Request is blocked and fail-closed policy is enforced.</p>
        </div>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-arrows" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 8; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <span class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-branch">↓</span>
          <span class="wf-arrow wf-arrow-branch">↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-evidence wf-node wf-evidence" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 9">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Decision Evidence</p>
          <p>Structured decision record retained for reviewer inspection.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Decision Evidence</h2>
    <p>
      The workflow emits structured enforcement records only after BeaconGuard has decided allow or deny. Reviewers inspect the decision signal,
      enforcement fields, trust validation, and evidence hashes to determine exactly what control path executed.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/proof-evidence">Review Decision Evidence</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/security">Security</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/reviewer-kit">Reviewer Kit</a>
    </div>
  </section>

<style>
  .workflow-grid {
  --decision-step-width: 300px;
    --evidence-width: min(300px, 100%);
    width: max-content;
    max-width: none;
    min-width: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, var(--decision-step-width));
  gap: 2rem 0.78rem;
  align-items: stretch;
  justify-items: stretch;
  justify-content: stretch;
    
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.workflow-frame {
  width: max-content;
  max-width: none;
  margin: 1.8rem auto 0;
  display: block;
  overflow: visible;
  padding: 0.5rem 0.65rem 0.65rem;
}

.workflow-frame > .workflow-grid {
  margin: 0 auto;
  overflow: visible;
}

  .wf-branch-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.9rem;
    width: min(100%, 700px);
    justify-items: stretch;
    justify-content: center;
    justify-self: center;
  }

  .wf-branch-row .wf-branch-step {
    width: min(300px, 100%);
  }

  .wf-branch-arrows {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    align-items: center;
    justify-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    justify-self: center;
    width: min(100%, 700px);
    padding: 0 0.1rem;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .wf-node {
    min-height: 120px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  width: var(--decision-step-width);
  max-width: 100%;
  min-width: 300px;
    justify-self: center;
  }

  .wf-sequence-step {
  width: var(--decision-step-width);
  max-width: 100%;
  min-width: 300px;
  justify-self: center;
}

  .wf-evidence {
  width: var(--decision-step-width);
  max-width: 100%;
  min-width: 300px;
  justify-self: center;
  grid-column: 1 / -1 !important;
  border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.45);
  background-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.06);
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.22);
}

  .wf-branch-step {
  width: var(--decision-step-width);
  max-width: 100%;
  min-width: 300px;
  justify-self: center;
}

  .wf-arrow {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    min-height: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .wf-cell-spacer {
    min-height: 1.5rem;
  }

  .wf-arrow-right {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .wf-arrow-down {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .wf-arrow-branch {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    min-height: 1.15rem;
    justify-self: center;
    transform: none;
  }

  .wf-branch-arrows .wf-arrow-branch:last-of-type {
    transform: none;
  }

  .wf-arrow-right {
    justify-self: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .workflow-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.2rem 0;
    }

    .workflow-grid > * {
      grid-column: 1 !important;
      grid-row: auto !important;
    }

    .wf-arrow,
    .wf-cell-spacer {
      min-height: 1rem;
    }

    .wf-arrow-top,
    .wf-arrow-bottom,
    .wf-arrow-branch {
      transform: none !important;
      min-height: 1rem;
      width: 100%;
      justify-content: center;
    }
  }
</style>
</BaseLayout>
